{"title":"Explore Oregon’s Diverse Landscapes with Summit Cycling Adventures","link":"https://bikerumor.com/guided-bike-tour-oregon-road-gravel-bicycle-rides/","date":1690483097000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-gravel-roads-for-days.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure gravel roads for days\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-gravel-roads-for-days.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-gravel-roads-for-days-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-gravel-roads-for-days-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-gravel-roads-for-days-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-gravel-roads-for-days-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-gravel-roads-for-days-400x225.jpeg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-gravel-roads-for-days-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></p>\n<p>Have you always wanted to experience the amazingly diverse landscapes of Oregon on a bicycle? Not sure where to start? That’s where Summit Cycling Adventures comes in, as they’ve added four new, <a href=\"https://www.summitbiketours.com/\" target=\"_blank\">fully supported, professionally guided bike tours</a> in Oregon. So, now you can just show up with your bike and let Summit lead the way through Oregon’s forests, high deserts, mountains, and coasts. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-logo.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"611\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-logo-800x611.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-logo-800x611.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-logo-297x227.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-logo-120x92.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-logo-768x587.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-logo.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>Photo c. Summit Cycling Adventures</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When using Summit Cycling Adventures, you’ll be able to take advantage of tapping into local knowledge while discovering backroads, nature reserves, and local “secret spots”, while soaking in the natural environment on road and gravel rides. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-touring.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-touring-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure touring\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-touring-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-touring-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-touring-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-touring-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-touring-400x225.jpeg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-touring-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-touring.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-mountian-road.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"449\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-mountian-road-800x449.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure mountian road\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-mountian-road-800x449.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-mountian-road-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-mountian-road-120x67.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-mountian-road-768x431.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-mountian-road-400x225.jpeg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-mountian-road-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-mountian-road.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-winding-road.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-winding-road-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure winding road\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-winding-road-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-winding-road-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-winding-road-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-winding-road-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-winding-road-400x225.jpeg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-winding-road-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-winding-road.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>“<em>I wanted to share my home state in a way that feels like exploring</em>,” says founder and ride leader Marc McConnell. “<em>Epic rides are mixed with gorgeous sights and fun side trips that offer a more memorable experience, challenging your body and refreshing your spirit</em>.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-big-redwoods.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-big-redwoods-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure big redwoods\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-big-redwoods-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-big-redwoods-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-big-redwoods-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-big-redwoods-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-big-redwoods-400x225.jpeg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-big-redwoods-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-big-redwoods.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-cascades.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-cascades-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure cascades\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-cascades-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-cascades-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-cascades-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-cascades-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-cascades-400x225.jpeg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-cascades-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-cascades.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Summit Cycling Adventures says that they’ve intentionally integrated side excursions into the day’s ride. The objective is to not get stuck into just riding from point A to point B, but exploring the points in between. On the tours, you’ll be seeing hot springs, and waterfalls, taking short hikes through Redwoods, lava field lakes, and even stopping for coffee and beers. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>“I created Summit Cycling Adventures to help adventurous riders enjoy that same experience without having to figure out all the logistics, routing, meals, and gear transport for themselves. Now you can just show up and have fun!”</em> – Marc McConnel</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-crater-lake.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"449\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-crater-lake-800x449.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure crater lake\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-crater-lake-800x449.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-crater-lake-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-crater-lake-120x67.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-crater-lake-768x431.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-crater-lake-400x225.jpeg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-crater-lake-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-crater-lake.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-Redwoods.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"1067\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-Redwoods-800x1067.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure Redwoods\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-Redwoods-800x1067.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-Redwoods-225x300.jpeg 225w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-Redwoods-90x120.jpeg 90w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-Redwoods-768x1024.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-Redwoods.jpeg 960w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Visiting Famous Landmarks</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Carter Lake National Park</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cascade Mountains</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Grove of the Titans</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Steen’s Summit</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Alvord Desert Hot Springs</li>\n\n\n\n<li>North Umpqua River</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Many more…</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"601\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-800x601.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure tasty food\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-800x601.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-768x577.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food.jpeg 1061w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-2.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"602\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-2-800x602.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure tasty food 2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-2-800x602.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-2-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-2-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-2-768x578.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-2.jpeg 1170w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-3.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-3-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Summit Cycling Adventure tasty food 3\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-3-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-3-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-3-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-3-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Summit-Cycling-Adventure-tasty-food-3.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>“The tours ranging from 4-5 days are offered throughout Summer and Fall for up to six riders per tour. All meals and accommodations are provided, along with a fully stocked sag trailer to transport you and your gear. McConnel is a NOLS Wilderness First Responder, and the support vehicles are well-equipped to keep you and your bike running”.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Four distinct routes are offered to provide “something for everyone”. There will be plenty of snack stops and complete GOS routes provided for each day’s ride. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are limited spots remaining for 2023.  You can check the website below for prices, dates, and availability and to book your next adventure.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.summitbiketours.com/\" target=\"_blank\">SummitBikeTours.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/guided-bike-tour-oregon-road-gravel-bicycle-rides/\">Explore Oregon’s Diverse Landscapes with Summit Cycling Adventures</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d1d74c821a977ff4e5bda58da459b62b559234ebc69425951efb7ea06502109c","category":"Cycling"}